nib.text:
A man was fatally shot in Frogtown Wednesday morning.

Police responded to reports of a shooting inside a residence in the 700 block of Edmund Avenue at approximately 3:30 a.m.

Upon arrival, officers located a man in his 20s who was shot in the back.

Medics rushed him to an area hospital where he was later pronounced deceased, according to the [Pioneer Press](https://www.twincities.com/2022/05/04/police-investigating-fatal-shooting-in-st-pauls-frogtown/).

Sgt. Natalie Davis, a police spokeswoman, said multiple people were being interviewed.

No arrests have been made.

Police urge anyone with information to contact the homicide unit at 651-266-5650.

Homicide detectives are investigating.
